name: Apple Spice Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground allspice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'warm water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'apples - peeled, cored and chopped'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raisins'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "confectioners' sugar for dusting"}
steps: Gather all ingredients. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Butter a 10-inch tube pan.. Cover raisins with warm water and let soak for 10 minutes; drain.. Whisk flour, spices, and salt together in a bowl; set aside.. Beat butter and sugar together in a large bowl until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla. Stir baking soda and 1 tablespoon warm water together until smooth; stir into sugar mixture.. Mix in flour mixture, apples, and strained raisins until well blended.. Pour batter into prepared pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean, about 1 hour. Cool cake in pan.. Once cool, shake pan to loosen cake. Turn onto plate, and dust with confectioners' sugar.

name: Fresh Pear Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'peeled, cored and chopped pears'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sifted all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg whites'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Combine pears and sugar in a large bowl; let stand for one hour.. Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Spray a 10-inch Bundt pan with non-stick cooking spray.. Slightly beat egg whites; combine with oil, chopped pecans, and pear mixture.. Mix flour, salt, baking soda, nutmeg, cinnamon, and cloves together; stir into pear mixture. Pour batter into the prepared Bundt pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean, about 1 hour and 10 minutes. Let cool on a wire rack for 10 minutes before removing from the pan.. Invert carefully onto a serving plate or rack and let cool completely.

name: Best Carrot Cake Ever
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'grated carrots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raisins'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'crushed pineapple, drained'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Combine grated carrots and brown sugar in a medium bowl. Let sit for 1 hour, then stir in raisins.. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour two 10-inch round cake pans. Beat eggs in a large bowl until light.. Gradually beat in white sugar, oil, and vanilla. Stir in pineapple.. Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, and salt in a separate bowl, then stir into egg mixture until absorbed.. Stir in carrot mixture and walnuts. Pour evenly into the prepared pans.. Bake in the preheated oven until an inserted toothpick comes out clean, 45 to 50 minutes.. Cool for 10 minutes before removing cake layers from the pans; let cool completely.

name: Moist, Tender Spice Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'bleached all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground allspice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'large eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, softened until easily spreadable'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'dark brown sugar'}
steps: Adjust the oven rack to the middle position; preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and lightly flour a metal or disposable foil 9x13-inch pan.. Whisk flour, cornstarch, baking powder, ginger, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice, cloves, and salt in a large bowl. Mix milk, eggs, and vanilla extract in a 2-cup measuring cup.. Beat softened butter into flour mixture in a large bowl with an electric mixer, first on low, then medium, until mixture forms pebble-sized pieces. Add about 1/3 of the milk mixture and beat on low until smooth. Add remaining milk mixture in two stages; beat on medium speed until batter is just smooth. Add brown sugar; beat until just incorporated, about 30 seconds. Pour batter into the prepared pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 40 minutes. Cool briefly on a wire rack, then run a table knife around the edges to loosen. Invert carefully onto a serving plate or cooling rack. Let cool completely.

name: Buttery Cinnamon Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1 ⅓', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shortening'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and lightly flour a 10-inch Bundt pan.. Make the cake: Stir flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and salt together in a bowl.. Beat sugar, shortening, and vanilla in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.. Add eggs, one at a time, beating for at least 1 minute after each addition.. Beat in flour mixture alternately with milk.. Pour batter into the prepared pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean, 40 to 45 minutes.. While the cake is baking, make the syrup: Combine sugar, water, butter, vanilla, and cinnamon in a saucepan over medium-low heat. Cook and stir until butter melts; keep warm.. Remove cake from the oven and let cool in the pan for 10 minutes. Invert warm cake carefully onto a serving plate or cooling rack.. Use a fork to poke holes around the top of the cake.. Pour warm syrup over the top and sides, making sure it goes into the holes. Serve after about 30 minutes, while still warm.

name: Sugar-Free Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'raisins'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened applesauce'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'liquid sweetener'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.. Combine water and raisins in a saucepan over medium heat. Simmer until water is absorbed; set aside to cool.. Mix together applesauce, oil, eggs, liquid sweetener, and vanilla in a large bowl until well combined. Sift in flour, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg, and salt; stir until just combined. Mix in raisins and nuts. Pour batter into the prepared pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of cake comes out clean, about 1 hour.

name: Great Canadian Heinz Ketchup Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Heinz Tomato Ketchup'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'red food coloring'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': '3/4 cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'packed dark brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'brick-style cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'powdered sugar'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C). Grease two 9-inch round cake pans and line the bottoms with parchment paper.. Make the cake: Whisk flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, nutmeg, and ginger together in a bowl. Mix ketchup, water, and food coloring together in a separate bowl.. Beat butter in a large bowl with an electric mixer until smooth. Blend in sugar until creamy, then mix in eggs, one at a time, until incorporated. Add flour mixture in two batches on low speed, alternating with ketchup mixture, scraping down the bowl as needed, until well combined. Increase the speed to medium-high and beat for 1 minute. Divide batter evenly between the prepared pans.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 30 minutes. Cool in the pans on a wire rack for 15 minutes, then run a table knife around the edges to loosen. Invert each layer carefully onto the wire rack. Let cool completely, about 15 more minutes.. While the cake layers are cooling, make the frosting: Beat cream cheese, butter, and vanilla in a mixing bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed until smooth, about 2 minutes. Gradually mix in powdered sugar on low speed, scraping the bowl as needed, then beat on high speed until fluffy.. Place one cooled cake layer onto a serving plate. Cover with frosting and spread to the edges. Place remaining cake layer on top. Frost the sides of the cake, then finish by frosting the top.

name: Cake Mixes From Scratch and Variations
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 ⅓', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shortening'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 9x13-inch baking dish.. For a Yellow Cake: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt in a large bowl. Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs. Add milk, eggs, and vanilla. Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 1 minute, then on high for 2 minutes, scraping the bowl frequently. Pour batter into the prepared baking dish.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, 25 to 30 minutes.

name: Moist Apple Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '5', 'unit': None, 'name': 'apples - peeled, cored and sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease and flour a 9x13-inch pan.. Sift flour, salt, cinnamon, and baking powder together; set aside.. Beat eggs and sugar together in a large bowl with an electric mixer on high speed until light in color, about 10 to 15 minutes; beat in oil until combined. Add flour mixture and mix well. Add vanilla and fold in apples and nuts. Pour cake batter into prepared pan.. Mix 4 teaspoons sugar with 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a small bowl; sprinkle over cake.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into center of the cake comes out clean, about 50 to 60 minutes.

name: Apple Cake with Caramel Glaze
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'Granny Smith apples - peeled, cored and chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9-inch Bundt pan.. Beat sugar, oil, vanilla, and eggs in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and salt; stir into batter just until blended. Fold in apples and walnuts using a spoon. Pour into the prepared pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the crown or the cake comes out clean, about 1 hour to 1 hour 20 minutes. Allow cake to cool in pan for about 15 minutes then invert on to a wire rack.. To make the caramel glaze: Heat butter, milk, and brown sugar in a small saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar, then remove from the heat. Drizzle over warm cake.

name: Carrot Cake with PHILLY Cream Cheese Icing
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'MAGIC Baking Powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'dash', 'name': 'Dash of ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'granulated sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'grated carrots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(19 ounce) can', 'name': 'crushed pineapple, well drained'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts or pecans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(250 g) package', 'name': 'PHILADELPHIA Brick Cream Cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'icing sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'grated lemon peel'}
steps: Cake: Heat oven to 350 degrees F. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, spices and salt in medium bowl; set aside. Beat eggs and oil in large bowl with wire whisk until well blended. Gradually add granulated sugar, mixing until blended. Add flour mixture, carrots, pineapple and walnuts; mix well. Pour into greased and floured 12-cup fluted tube pan or 10-inch (3-L) tube pan.. Bake 50 min. to 1 hour or until wooden toothpick inserted in centre comes out clean. Cool 10 min.; loosen from sides of pan with spatula or knife and gently remove cake. Cool completely on wire rack.. Icing: Beat cream cheese and butter in large bowl with electric mixer until well blended. Gradually add icing sugar, juice and peel, beating until well blended after each addition. Spread on top of cake. Store leftover cake in refrigerator.

name: Tomato Soup Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'condensed tomato soup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'self-rising flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raisins'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Lightly grease a 10-inch square baking dish. Combine tomato soup and baking soda in a bowl; set aside.. Beat sugar, butter, egg, cinnamon, cloves, and salt in a large bowl with an electric mixer until smooth. Mix in tomato soup and soda mixture; stir in flour and raisins. Pour cake batter into a greased baking dish.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 1 hour.

name: Mother's Applesauce Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '3 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'unsweetened applesauce'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raisins'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dates, pitted and chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': "sifted confectioners' sugar"}
steps: Preheat oven to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). Grease and flour a tube pan.. Whisk together flour, salt, cinnamon, cloves, and soda. Set aside.. Cream together 1/2 cup butter and 2 cups brown sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Mix in eggs. Add flour mixture into creamed mixture alternately with applesauce, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in the raisins, dates, and walnuts. Pour batter into prepared pan.. Bake in preheated oven until a tester inserted in the center of the cake comes out clean, about 1 1/2 hours. Cool on wire rack.. To make icing, melt 1/2 cup butter or margarine in a small saucepan over low heat; stir in 1 cup brown sugar. Boil for 2 minutes. Stir in milk, and continue to stir until the mixture returns to a boil. Remove from heat, and cool for 5 minutes. Beat in vanilla and confectioners' sugar. Frost cooled cake.

name: Grandma Snyder's Oatmeal Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'boiling water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1 ⅓', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'melted butter'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'evaporated milk'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'flaked coconut'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: Pour water over oats, let stand.. Cream 1/2 cup butter or margarine and sugars. Add eggs and blend in a large mixing bowl. Sift the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg together. Add to sugars and egg mixture. Add vanilla and oats mixture, blend well.. Pour batter into a 9 x 13 inch pan.. Bake in a preheated 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) oven for 30-40 minutes.. To Make Icing: Mix together 6 tablespoons melted butter, 1 1/2 cups brown sugar, 3/4 cup evaporated milk, coconuts, nuts, and 1 teaspoon vanilla.. Pour this coconut concoction over the hot cake.. Put cake under broiler, and watch close so nuts don't burn, about 5-10 minutes. Serve hot or let cool. Enjoy.

name: Easy Raisin Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raisins'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '1 ¾', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease one 10 x 10 inch baking pan.. In a large saucepan boil the raising with the water for 10 minutes. Add the butter or margarine and let cool.. In the same pan add the flour, soda, salt, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, and chopped nuts (optional), mix well and pour batter into a lightly greased 10x10 inch baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) for 35 minutes. Serves 8 to 12.

name: German Apple Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'apples - peeled, cored and diced'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 9x13-inch cake pan.. Beat oil and eggs in a mixing bowl with an electric mixer until creamy. Add sugar and vanilla; beat well.. Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, and salt in a bowl. Slowly add flour mixture to egg mixture; mix until combined. The batter will be very thick. Fold in apples by hand using a wooden spoon. Spread batter into the prepared pan.. Bake cake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean, about 45 minutes. Cool cake on a wire rack.

name: Applesauce Cake VI
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'applesauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 10 inch tube pan. Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Set aside.. In a large bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Make a well in the center and pour in the eggs, sugar, oil, applesauce and vanilla. name: Nutmeg Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, room temperature'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'buttermilk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cream'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': "confectioners' sugar"}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly grease 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.. When cool, frost with your favorite Cream Cheese Frosting.

steps: Place raisins, lemon rind, and whiskey in a small bowl; set aside to soak overnight.. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line the bottom of an 8-inch square cake pan with parchment paper that is buttered and dusted with flour. Sift flour, salt, cloves, and baking powder into a bowl; set aside.. Cream butter and sugar together in a large bowl until light and fluffy. Add egg yolks and beat well. Quickly beat in flour mixture. Stir in soaked raisins.. In a separate clean bowl, whip egg whites until stiff; fold into cake batter. Pour into the prepared pan and bake in the preheated oven for 45 to 60 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into center of cake comes out clean. Cool cake on a wire rack.. To make glaze: Mix lemon juice, confectioners' sugar, and just enough whiskey and warm water so that you can drizzle icing over cake.

name: Coconut-Topped Oatmeal Cake

name: Raw Apple Cake

steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F(175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 9x13-inch baking pan.. Make the cake: Whisk oil and eggs together in a bowl. steps: Place an oven rack in an upper position in the oven. Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a 10-inch fluted tube pan (such as Bundt) with cooking spray.. name: Fig Spice Cake

steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.. Place dried figs into a saucepan and cover with water. name: Sausage Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'pork sausage'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sifted all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pumpkin pie spice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cold, strong, brewed coffee'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'raisins'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) grease and flour a 9 inch Bundt pan. Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand 5 minutes. Drain well and dry raisins with a cloth towel.. steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 9-inch square pan. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Set aside.. name: Zucchini Bars with Spice Frosting
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ⅓', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded zucchini'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped walnuts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese frosting'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Butter a 9x13-inch baking pan.. Make the zucchini bars: Mix brown sugar, butter, eggs, and vanilla extract together in a bowl. Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon, and cloves. Mix in zucchini and walnuts. Spread batter into the prepared baking pan.. name: Glazed Fig Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'buttermilk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh figs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'evaporated milk'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch dish.. Make the cake: Mix flour, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, baking soda, baking powder, and salt together in a bowl.. Cream sugar and butter in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Stir in eggs. Beat in flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, mixing just until incorporated. Fold in figs and pecans. Pour batter into the prepared pan.. Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean, about 1 hour. Remove from the oven and let cool, about 30 minutes.. Meanwhile, make the glaze: Combine butter, sugar, evaporated milk, and baking soda in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Continue to cook, without stirring, until the mixture turns brown and measures 240 degrees F (115 degrees C); a small amount of syrup dropped into cold water should form a soft ball that flattens when removed from the water and placed onto a flat surface.. Pour into a small bowl and beat until it thickens to a spreading consistency. Quickly spread icing onto the cooled cake.

steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease and flour a 12x18 inch pan.. In a large bowl, stir together the flour, cocoa, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon. name: Kim's Buttermilk Spice Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground allspice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'firmly packed dark brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'buttermilk, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': "confectioners' sugar"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'heavy cream'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9x13-inch baking pan.. Whisk together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cloves, nutmeg, and allspice in a bowl until well combined.. Cream together butter, brown sugar, and white sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time, mixing well after each addition. Mix in vanilla extract. Add in half of the flour mixture, and stir until just combined. Pour in buttermilk, and mix until just combined. Add in remaining flour mixture and mix until just combined. Pour batter into the prepared pan and spread into an even layer.. Bake in the preheated oven until the middle of the cake springs back lightly when touched, 40 to 45 minutes. Remove from the oven and allow the cake to cool completely before frosting.. For the frosting, cream butter in a large bowl until smooth. Add cream cheese and beat until thoroughly combined. Mix in confectioners' sugar, 1 cup at a time, and beat until smooth after each addition. Mix in vanilla and salt. Add in heavy cream and beat until frosting is smooth, about 2 minutes. Frost cooled cake as desired.

name: Cinnabon® Cupcakes
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sifted cake flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole milk at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'large egg whites at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'almond extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cold heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': "confectioners' sugar"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'drop', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon for sprinkling, or to taste'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease 24 cupcake cups or line with paper liners.. Melt 1/2 cup unsalted butter in a saucepan over low heat; stir brown sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon into butter until brown sugar has dissolved and cinnamon syrup is hot, about 2 minutes. Set aside.. Sift cake flour with baking powder and salt into a bowl. Whisk milk, egg whites, egg, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla extract, and almond extract together in a separate bowl. Mix 1/2 cup butter at room temperature with white sugar in a large bowl, using an electric mixer until pale yellow and creamy, about 5 minutes. Gradually beat flour mixture into creamed butter mixture, alternating with milk mixture, until batter is well blended. Continue beating for 2 more minutes.. Beat cold cream with an electric mixer and clean beaters in a chilled glass or metal bowl until the cream is fluffy and holds soft peaks, about 4 minutes; fold whipped cream into batter. Divide batter among the prepared cupcake cups, filling them about 2/3 full.. Spoon 1 teaspoon of cinnamon syrup into batter in each cupcake cup. Set remaining cinnamon syrup aside.. Bake cupcakes in the preheated oven until lightly browned and a toothpick inserted into the center of a cupcake comes out with moist crumbs, about 16 minutes. Remove cupcakes from pans and let cool upside down on racks.. Place saucepan with remaining cinnamon syrup over medium heat, stir in pecans, and bring mixture to a low boil. Immediately remove from heat and pour pecan mixture out onto a wooden cutting board. Let pecan mixture cool completely and chop the pecan candy finely.. Beat 1/4 cup butter at room temperature with an electric mixer in a bowl until soft and creamy; beat in cream cheese until blended. Add confectioners' sugar and a drop of vanilla extract and continue to beat on high speed until frosting is fluffy, at least 5 minutes.. Frost cooled cupcakes with frosting and decorate each with a pinch of chopped pecan candy and a sprinkle of cinnamon.

steps: To make cupcakes: Blend the eggs, oil, sugar, and pumpkin in a large mixing bowl; set aside. Stir together dry ingredients in a separate bowl. steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Line a 9x13-inch baking pan with parchment paper.. Add prunes to a saucepan; cover with water and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and let stand for 10 minutes. steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). In a bowl, lightly mix the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, and salt until thoroughly combined..
